# Chapter 11: Adding a Frontend (Making It Look Real)

*In which we stop looking at JSON and start looking at a real interface.*

## Why Frontend Matters

A backend API that returns JSON is impressive to developers. It is impressive to literally nobody else.

Real users interact with interfaces — buttons, text inputs, visual feedback. If you want someone other than a developer to use your app, you need a frontend.

This chapter builds the Study Buddy UI. We'll use React — the most widely-used frontend framework — but we'll keep it simple. No complex state management. No fancy patterns. Just a clean, working interface.

---

## Setting Up the Frontend

We'll use Vite — a fast, modern build tool that sets up a React project in seconds:

```bash
# From your study-buddy project root
npm create vite@latest frontend -- --template react
cd frontend
npm install
```

This creates a `frontend/` folder with a working React app.

Also install a few things we'll use:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install axios  # For making API calls (easier than raw fetch)
```

Your project structure is now:

```
study-buddy/
├── src/                    # Backend
│   ├── index.js
│   ├── routes/quiz.js
│   └── prompts/system.js
├── frontend/               # Frontend
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── App.jsx         # Main app component
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   ├── TextInput.jsx
│   │   │   ├── QuizDisplay.jsx
│   │   │   └── LoadingSpinner.jsx
│   │   └── main.jsx
│   ├── index.html
│   └── package.json
├── .env
└── package.json
```

---

## The Main App Component

```jsx
// frontend/src/App.jsx
import { useState } from 'react';
import axios from 'axios';
import TextInput from './components/TextInput';
import QuizDisplay from './components/QuizDisplay';
import LoadingSpinner from './components/LoadingSpinner';
import './App.css';

const API_URL = 'http://localhost:3001/api';

function App() {
  const [text, setText] = useState('');
  const [quiz, setQuiz] = useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);

  const generateQuiz = async () => {
    if (!text.trim()) return;

    setLoading(true);
    setError(null);
    setQuiz(null);

    try {
      const response = await axios.post(`${API_URL}/generate-quiz`, { text });
      setQuiz(response.data);
    } catch (err) {
      const message = err.response?.data?.error || 'Something went wrong. Please try again.';
      setError(message);
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  const reset = () => {
    setQuiz(null);
    setError(null);
  };

  return (
    <div className="app">
      <header className="app-header">
        <h1>📚 StudyBuddy</h1>
        <p>Paste your notes. Get quiz questions. Actually learn.</p>
      </header>

      <main className="app-main">
        {!quiz && !loading && (
          <TextInput
            text={text}
            onChange={setText}
            onSubmit={generateQuiz}
            disabled={loading}
          />
        )}

        {loading && <LoadingSpinner />}

        {error && (
          <div className="error-message">
            <p>{error}</p>
            <button onClick={reset}>Try Again</button>
          </div>
        )}

        {quiz && !loading && (
          <QuizDisplay quiz={quiz} onReset={reset} />
        )}
      </main>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

---

## The Text Input Component

```jsx
// frontend/src/components/TextInput.jsx
const MAX_CHARS = 8000;

function TextInput({ text, onChange, onSubmit, disabled }) {
  const charCount = text.length;
  const isOverLimit = charCount > MAX_CHARS;
  const isTooShort = charCount > 0 && charCount < 100;

  return (
    <div className="text-input-container">
      <label htmlFor="study-text">
        Paste your study material below:
      </label>

      <textarea
        id="study-text"
        value={text}
        onChange={(e) => onChange(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Paste a chapter, article, or set of notes here... (at least 100 characters)"
        rows={12}
        disabled={disabled}
        className={isOverLimit ? 'over-limit' : ''}
      />

      <div className="input-footer">
        <span className={`char-count ${isOverLimit ? 'over' : ''}`}>
          {charCount.toLocaleString()} / {MAX_CHARS.toLocaleString()} characters
        </span>

        {isTooShort && (
          <span className="hint">Need a bit more text to generate good questions.</span>
        )}

        <button
          onClick={onSubmit}
          disabled={disabled || isOverLimit || charCount < 100}
          className="generate-btn"
        >
          Generate Quiz →
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default TextInput;
```

---

## The Quiz Display Component

This is where the magic becomes visible:

```jsx
// frontend/src/components/QuizDisplay.jsx
import { useState } from 'react';

function QuizDisplay({ quiz, onReset }) {
  const [answers, setAnswers] = useState({});
  const [submitted, setSubmitted] = useState(false);

  const handleSelect = (questionIndex, option) => {
    if (submitted) return;
    setAnswers(prev => ({ ...prev, [questionIndex]: option }));
  };

  const handleSubmit = () => {
    setSubmitted(true);
  };

  const score = submitted
    ? quiz.questions.filter((q, i) => answers[i] === q.correct).length
    : null;

  const allAnswered = quiz.questions.every((_, i) => answers[i] !== undefined);

  return (
    <div className="quiz-display">
      <div className="quiz-header">
        <h2>Your Quiz</h2>
        <button onClick={onReset} className="back-btn">← New Text</button>
      </div>

      {submitted && (
        <div className="score-banner">
          Score: {score} / {quiz.questions.length}
          {score === quiz.questions.length && ' 🎉 Perfect!'}
        </div>
      )}

      {quiz.questions.map((q, qIndex) => (
        <div key={qIndex} className={`question-card ${submitted ? 'submitted' : ''}`}>
          <p className="question-text">
            <strong>Q{qIndex + 1}.</strong> {q.question}
          </p>

          <div className="options">
            {Object.entries(q.options).map(([letter, text]) => {
              const isSelected = answers[qIndex] === letter;
              const isCorrect = letter === q.correct;
              let optionClass = 'option';

              if (submitted) {
                if (isCorrect) optionClass += ' correct';
                else if (isSelected && !isCorrect) optionClass += ' incorrect';
              } else if (isSelected) {
                optionClass += ' selected';
              }

              return (
                <button
                  key={letter}
                  className={optionClass}
                  onClick={() => handleSelect(qIndex, letter)}
                >
                  <span className="option-letter">{letter}.</span>
                  {text}
                </button>
              );
            })}
          </div>

          {submitted && (
            <div className="explanation">
              <strong>Explanation:</strong> {q.explanation}
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      ))}

      {!submitted && (
        <button
          onClick={handleSubmit}
          disabled={!allAnswered}
          className="submit-btn"
        >
          {allAnswered ? 'Submit Answers' : `Answer all questions to submit (${Object.keys(answers).length}/${quiz.questions.length} answered)`}
        </button>
      )}

      {submitted && (
        <button onClick={onReset} className="try-again-btn">
          Try with New Text →
        </button>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

export default QuizDisplay;
```

